196
00:26:20,345 --> 00:26:21,425
Xu Meng and I

197
00:26:23,545 --> 00:26:25,865
met through pen pal correspondence

198
00:26:27,145 --> 00:26:28,745
in the spring of 1995.

199
00:26:30,345 --> 00:26:32,905
The two of us share the same birth date.

200
00:26:33,505 --> 00:26:37,145
At the time, we were listed together
in a pen pal column in a magazine.

201
00:26:38,785 --> 00:26:40,945
She said her mother's surname
was also Qiao.

202
00:26:41,945 --> 00:26:44,225
She was born two hours later than I,

203
00:26:45,865 --> 00:26:47,305
so she called me "sister".

204
00:26:48,785 --> 00:26:51,185
Our family situations
were very similar as well.

205
00:26:52,745 --> 00:26:54,025
She didn't have a mother,

206
00:26:55,025 --> 00:26:56,385
and I didn't have a father.

207
00:26:58,105 --> 00:27:00,865
We both wanted to build
a complete family again.

208
00:27:07,345 --> 00:27:08,305
Qing.

209
00:27:08,385 --> 00:27:09,385
-Yes?
-Want an ice pop?

210
00:27:09,465 --> 00:27:11,145
No, thanks. You have it, Mom.

211
00:27:11,225 --> 00:27:13,145
<i>YOUTH DIGEST</i>

212
00:27:13,225 --> 00:27:14,625
<i>In August that year,</i>

213
00:27:15,825 --> 00:27:17,505
<i>we made a plan</i>

214
00:27:17,585 --> 00:27:19,945
<i>to join a tour group to Mount Wu together.</i>

215
00:27:21,105 --> 00:27:23,065
KUNPENG TRAVEL AGENCY

216
00:27:24,705 --> 00:27:26,905
<i>It wasn't just</i>
<i>so the two of us could meet.</i>

217
00:27:28,025 --> 00:27:30,305
<i>It was also actually</i>
<i>to set our parents up.</i>

218
00:27:30,385 --> 00:27:31,825
PEN PAL MATCH: NIHAI PIANXIAN

219
00:27:32,425 --> 00:27:33,545
<i>If it worked out,</i>

220
00:27:34,105 --> 00:27:36,345
<i>we could become a family</i>

221
00:27:39,185 --> 00:27:41,145
<i>and become real sisters.</i>

222
00:27:41,785 --> 00:27:42,625
-Very nice.
-Okay.

223
00:27:47,185 --> 00:27:49,505
Okay. Let's do a roll call.

224
00:27:49,585 --> 00:27:51,345
-Wang Zusheng?
-Here.

225
00:27:52,345 --> 00:27:54,305
-Qiao Suqing?
-Here.

226
00:27:56,345 --> 00:27:57,785
-Fang Xiuhong?
-Present.

227
00:27:58,425 --> 00:28:00,825
-Xu Zhihong?
-Right here.

228
00:28:01,345 --> 00:28:03,745
-Xu Meng?
-Here too.

229
00:28:07,585 --> 00:28:09,785
Everyone, stay close. Watch your step.

230
00:28:10,825 --> 00:28:11,865
Everyone,

231
00:28:11,945 --> 00:28:13,465
right beneath our feet

232
00:28:13,545 --> 00:28:15,865
-It flied away!
-is the famous Mount Wu Slot.

233
00:28:15,945 --> 00:28:18,665
Now, remember when walking
on the suspension bridge,

234
00:28:18,745 --> 00:28:20,985
no running or jumping. Stay safe.

235
00:28:21,065 --> 00:28:22,145
Those in the back, please keep up.

236
00:28:31,385 --> 00:28:32,345
Here.

237
00:28:33,465 --> 00:28:34,665
Wear mine.

238
00:28:37,505 --> 00:28:39,985
Alright, everyone.
We're about to head up the mountain.

239
00:28:40,065 --> 00:28:41,785
Watch your step and stay safe.

240
00:28:51,945 --> 00:28:54,265
Everyone, we must be careful
with our footing.

241
00:28:54,345 --> 00:28:56,065
The path is a bit slippery today.

242
00:29:00,065 --> 00:29:01,145
What's wrong?

243
00:29:01,225 --> 00:29:03,105
-Are you okay?
-Why is the fog so thick?

244
00:29:03,185 --> 00:29:05,425
-I can't even see the road.
-Everyone, don't panic.

245
00:29:06,025 --> 00:29:08,265
This kind of weather
is very common on Mount Wu.

246
00:29:08,345 --> 00:29:09,345
How about this?

247
00:29:09,425 --> 00:29:11,225
Let us all hold hands.

248
00:29:13,585 --> 00:29:15,465
Sister, don't be afraid.

249
00:29:15,545 --> 00:29:16,385
I'm right here with you.

250
00:29:21,305 --> 00:29:22,385
Steady now.

251
00:29:23,025 --> 00:29:23,945
Mom…

252
00:29:24,705 --> 00:29:26,465
I'm having a hard time breathing.

253
00:29:26,545 --> 00:29:27,545
Come and rest here for a bit.

254
00:29:28,145 --> 00:29:29,185
Sit down.

255
00:29:32,545 --> 00:29:34,625
Hey, we really can't stay here.

256
00:29:34,705 --> 00:29:36,425
Once it gets dark, it'll be freezing cold.

257
00:29:36,505 --> 00:29:38,465
What's wrong with waiting a moment?

258
00:29:38,545 --> 00:29:39,865
Can't you be a little considerate?

259
00:29:39,945 --> 00:29:41,625
If you want to die,
don't drag us down with you.

260
00:29:41,705 --> 00:29:43,665
Why do you care about her?
Let's just get moving.

261
00:29:43,745 --> 00:29:44,785
Fine. You guys rest for a while,

262
00:29:44,865 --> 00:29:46,545
-but catch up quickly.
-Hurry up.

263
00:29:48,745 --> 00:29:49,665
-<i>I was unconscious then.</i>
-Qing!

264
00:29:51,185 --> 00:29:53,825
As for what happened later,
I have no idea.

265
00:29:55,625 --> 00:29:56,865
When I woke up,

266
00:29:57,385 --> 00:29:59,145
Xu Meng and her father were gone.

267
00:30:00,505 --> 00:30:02,305
I was completely dazed.

268
00:30:03,065 --> 00:30:05,825
I thought my mom
had accidentally fallen off the cliff.

269
00:30:07,345 --> 00:30:09,345
It felt like in the blink of an eye…

270
00:30:11,145 --> 00:30:12,305
Mom was gone.

271
00:30:13,785 --> 00:30:15,025
My home was gone.

272
00:30:17,425 --> 00:30:18,825
Everything was gone.

273
00:30:25,345 --> 00:30:28,425
When did you run into Xu Meng again?

274
00:30:29,145 --> 00:30:30,745
About half a year later.

275
00:30:32,385 --> 00:30:34,145
When I came to Weiyang back then,

276
00:30:36,465 --> 00:30:38,145
I stayed at Yao Baiyuan's place.

277
00:31:09,745 --> 00:31:11,025
<i>That night,</i>

278
00:31:12,065 --> 00:31:13,745
<i>we talked a lot.</i>

279
00:31:14,785 --> 00:31:16,065
<i>That's when I learned</i>

280
00:31:17,265 --> 00:31:19,065
<i>that after returning from Mount Wu,</i>

281
00:31:19,945 --> 00:31:21,345
<i>her life</i>

282
00:31:22,225 --> 00:31:24,345
<i>wasn't much better than mine.</i>

283
00:31:26,225 --> 00:31:29,625
PEACE AND LUCK TO ALL
WEALTH AND JOY TO HOME

284
00:31:30,825 --> 00:31:32,145
Where's the medicine? Medicine!

285
00:31:32,665 --> 00:31:33,705
Where did you hide the medicine?

286
00:31:36,465 --> 00:31:37,505
Where did you put the medicine?

287
00:31:39,385 --> 00:31:41,785
Medicine! Medicine! Where's the medicine?

288
00:31:43,025 --> 00:31:45,905
It's all your fault
that I've ended up like this!

289
00:31:46,505 --> 00:31:48,785
I need my medicine!

290
00:31:49,465 --> 00:31:50,465
You!

291
00:31:51,505 --> 00:31:53,025
-Dad, please stop hitting me!
-Get me my medicine!

292
00:31:53,105 --> 00:31:54,265
I was wrong, Dad!

293
00:31:54,865 --> 00:31:55,865
-Dad, please stop!
-I need my medicine!

294
00:31:55,945 --> 00:31:57,185
I was wrong, Dad!

295
00:31:57,265 --> 00:31:58,545
-Dad!
-Where is my medine?

296
00:31:59,065 --> 00:32:03,545
QIHUANG CLINIC

297
00:32:07,185 --> 00:32:08,585
Master Zhang,

298
00:32:09,385 --> 00:32:11,465
I'm here for the medicine. Master Zhang?

299
00:32:16,025 --> 00:32:17,265
Master Zhang.

300
00:32:20,665 --> 00:32:22,465
CARE AND VIRTUE, A HEALER'S HEART

301
00:32:37,665 --> 00:32:39,065
<i>Back then,</i>

302
00:32:40,385 --> 00:32:44,625
<i>we were like two elk caught in a snare.</i>

303
00:32:44,705 --> 00:32:47,025
<i>Neither of us could escape,</i>

304
00:32:47,105 --> 00:32:48,345
<i>and neither could help the other.</i>

305
00:32:49,345 --> 00:32:51,505
<i>All we could do</i>
<i>was watch each other in silence.</i>

306
00:32:53,865 --> 00:32:55,305
Six months later,

307
00:32:56,905 --> 00:32:58,665
I managed to escape first.

308
00:33:10,625 --> 00:33:11,545
Sister.

309
00:33:19,505 --> 00:33:20,345
A Chinese New Year's gift.

310
00:33:24,385 --> 00:33:25,785
Take a look.

311
00:33:28,025 --> 00:33:29,225
It's beautiful.

312
00:33:30,905 --> 00:33:31,745
It must have been expensive.

313
00:33:32,385 --> 00:33:34,905
It didn't cost anything.
Mr. Yao gave it to me.

314
00:33:39,665 --> 00:33:41,585
Happy Chinese New Year, Sister.

315
00:33:56,145 --> 00:33:57,025
He hit you again?

316
00:33:59,985 --> 00:34:02,945
Do you like this gift?

317
00:34:10,744 --> 00:34:11,585
I do.

318
00:34:29,665 --> 00:34:31,025
Happy Chinese New Year,

319
00:34:31,545 --> 00:34:32,545
Sister.

320
00:34:36,425 --> 00:34:37,945
Happy Chinese New Year.

321
00:35:39,465 --> 00:35:41,105
Sister, what's wrong?

322
00:35:42,505 --> 00:35:44,105
Yao is finally gone.

323
00:35:44,185 --> 00:35:46,105
Is there still something
making you unhappy?

324
00:35:47,385 --> 00:35:48,625
I was thinking,

325
00:35:50,585 --> 00:35:51,745
what's going to happen to you?

326
00:35:53,545 --> 00:35:55,985
When will you be able
to get away from the guy?

327
00:35:57,905 --> 00:36:02,185
Meng, why don't you move into my place?

328
00:36:04,985 --> 00:36:07,105
Don't go back to that house anymore.

329
00:36:10,705 --> 00:36:12,345
He's my father.

330
00:36:12,985 --> 00:36:14,705
I've owed him since the day I was born.

331
00:36:25,345 --> 00:36:29,185
I'm not as lucky as you.

332
00:36:31,185 --> 00:36:32,785
An "accident" like that

333
00:36:35,705 --> 00:36:37,705
doesn't happen that easily.

334
00:36:46,905 --> 00:36:48,625
So you didn't know

335
00:36:49,265 --> 00:36:52,625
that Yao Baiyuan
might have been killed by Xu Meng?

336
00:36:53,505 --> 00:36:56,265
At the time, I really thought
it was an accident.

337
00:36:56,905 --> 00:36:58,905
Then, how did Xu Zhihong die?

338
00:37:02,025 --> 00:37:05,945
Xu Meng said it was all for me.

339
00:37:15,305 --> 00:37:17,625
Dad, what are you doing?

340
00:37:17,705 --> 00:37:19,585
Close the door. Hurry up!

341
00:37:19,665 --> 00:37:20,745
Close it!

342
00:37:24,345 --> 00:37:26,545
Leave Weiyang. Pack your things right now.

343
00:37:26,625 --> 00:37:28,825
-We're leaving now.
-But Dad,

344
00:37:28,905 --> 00:37:31,025
why do we have to leave Weiyang?

345
00:37:31,105 --> 00:37:33,265
You ask why? I'll tell you why!

346
00:37:33,345 --> 00:37:37,585
Behind my back,
you took out so many shark loans.

347
00:37:37,665 --> 00:37:39,545
Those people are already at our doorstep.

348
00:37:40,185 --> 00:37:43,385
If we don't leave,
we're just staying here to die?

349
00:37:44,465 --> 00:37:46,665
I'll find a way to pay them back.

350
00:37:47,185 --> 00:37:48,185
Can we please not leave?

351
00:37:48,785 --> 00:37:49,705
Pay them with what?

352
00:37:50,225 --> 00:37:51,625
By selling yourself?

353
00:37:51,705 --> 00:37:54,745
That's enough. Go pack your clothes! Move!

354
00:37:54,825 --> 00:37:56,825
-Go!
-Dad, don't force me.

355
00:37:56,905 --> 00:37:58,705
You won't leave, and I'm "forcing" you?

356
00:37:58,785 --> 00:38:00,305
Is it because of the wretch?

357
00:38:01,825 --> 00:38:04,185
You ungrateful brat!

358
00:38:04,785 --> 00:38:06,985
I'm the one who gave you life.

359
00:38:07,625 --> 00:38:09,785
Go. You're coming with me.

360
00:38:11,025 --> 00:38:12,265
Dad, don't touch that.

361
00:38:13,065 --> 00:38:15,545
Did the wretch give you this outfit?

362
00:38:16,665 --> 00:38:17,705
Dad, don't.

363
00:38:17,785 --> 00:38:18,785
Let go of me.

364
00:38:18,865 --> 00:38:20,465
Let go. Let go!

365
00:38:21,065 --> 00:38:22,065
You won't come with me?

366
00:38:22,665 --> 00:38:24,545
-Are you coming?
-Dad, don't force me.

367
00:38:25,425 --> 00:38:26,385
I'm forcing you?

368
00:38:26,465 --> 00:38:28,745
I'm forcing you?

369
00:38:28,825 --> 00:38:30,625
You don't want to leave?

370
00:38:30,705 --> 00:38:33,625
That's fine. I'll go find
the wretch right now

371
00:38:33,705 --> 00:38:35,265
and beat her to death!

372
00:38:35,785 --> 00:38:37,505
Now, are you coming?

373
00:38:58,025 --> 00:39:00,585
The wretch…

374
00:39:00,665 --> 00:39:03,585
If it weren't for her back then,

375
00:39:03,665 --> 00:39:08,345
I wouldn't have ended up like this.

376
00:39:08,425 --> 00:39:10,385
I'm going to kill her.

377
00:39:10,985 --> 00:39:12,825
I'll kill her…

378
00:39:15,825 --> 00:39:16,945
Medicine…

379
00:39:17,025 --> 00:39:18,745
Medicine… Give it to me.

380
00:39:18,825 --> 00:39:20,065
Medicine…

381
00:39:21,705 --> 00:39:22,785
My medicine.

382
00:39:24,025 --> 00:39:24,945
Quick.

383
00:39:25,665 --> 00:39:28,065
Hurry… Get me my medicine.

384
00:39:46,825 --> 00:39:48,785
PENICILLIN V TABLETS

385
00:39:55,465 --> 00:39:56,785
What happened?

386
00:40:34,745 --> 00:40:35,785
Sister,

387
00:40:36,705 --> 00:40:40,145
when your mom fell off the cliff,
it wasn't an accident.

388
00:40:42,145 --> 00:40:43,865
He was the one who pushed her.

389
00:40:53,545 --> 00:40:56,025
Qing. Qing. Qing, what's wrong?

390
00:40:56,105 --> 00:40:57,145
-Sister.
-Qing.

391
00:40:57,225 --> 00:40:58,505
-<i>You fainted from the cold.</i>
-Sister,

392
00:40:58,585 --> 00:41:00,465
-<i>He tried to take your coat for warmth.</i>
-wake up.

393
00:41:01,465 --> 00:41:02,905
-Qing.
-Sister…

394
00:41:05,025 --> 00:41:06,105
What are you doing?

395
00:41:06,785 --> 00:41:08,185
She's not going to make it anyway.

396
00:41:08,265 --> 00:41:10,185
This coat should be given
to someone who can survive.

397
00:41:10,265 --> 00:41:12,025
What are you talking about?

398
00:41:12,105 --> 00:41:13,585
-Stop it.
-Let go.

399
00:41:13,665 --> 00:41:15,105
-Stop fighting.
-Stay out of this.

400
00:41:15,185 --> 00:41:18,625
<i>Your mom tried to stop him,</i>
<i>so he started wrestling with her.</i>

401
00:41:19,385 --> 00:41:20,345
Dad.

402
00:41:20,865 --> 00:41:21,825
Dad.

403
00:41:24,145 --> 00:41:25,025
Dad.

404
00:41:26,025 --> 00:41:27,225
Dad.

405
00:41:28,065 --> 00:41:29,425
Dad…

406
00:41:29,505 --> 00:41:32,625
Help. Is anyone there? Help.

407
00:41:32,705 --> 00:41:35,025
Help. Is anyone there?

408
00:41:35,105 --> 00:41:36,665
Help.

409
00:42:04,465 --> 00:42:06,785
<i>He thinks his illness is all our fault.</i>

410
00:42:07,505 --> 00:42:09,145
<i>He tortures me every day,</i>

411
00:42:09,225 --> 00:42:10,825
<i>and now he wants to come after you.</i>

412
00:42:11,505 --> 00:42:12,865
<i>I had no other choice.</i>

413
00:42:22,865 --> 00:42:25,185
PEACE AND LUCK TO ALL
WEALTH AND JOY TO HOME

414
00:42:49,745 --> 00:42:50,705
Sister,

415
00:42:52,705 --> 00:42:55,185
from now on, we are real sisters.

416
00:42:57,425 --> 00:42:59,345
I will protect you with my life.

417
00:43:21,865 --> 00:43:26,265
Xu, inside your place,
why is there all that banging?

418
00:43:26,345 --> 00:43:27,745
Is everything all right?

419
00:43:27,825 --> 00:43:30,185
My dad wanted to sell the large wardrobe.

420
00:43:30,265 --> 00:43:32,985
The door is too narrow,
so we couldn't get it out.

421
00:43:34,105 --> 00:43:36,465
So I'm trying to chip at the door frame.

422
00:43:39,825 --> 00:43:42,985
By the way, Uncle Wang, do you have…

423
00:43:43,065 --> 00:43:45,145
Oh, I've got mung bean soup on the stove.

424
00:43:45,225 --> 00:43:46,825
It's about to burn.

425
00:43:47,505 --> 00:43:48,745
It's burning.

426
00:44:09,345 --> 00:44:10,385
Take this

427
00:44:11,705 --> 00:44:13,065
back to my house.

428
00:44:17,025 --> 00:44:18,385
I'll protect you, too.

